The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, March 22, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Saturday, March 22, 2003				 																What to do this weekend				 																																	Applaud eight eminent writers who will receive the Rachana Samagra Award from the Bharatiya Bhasha Parishad on the Parishad premises at 10 am. A seminar on Challenges of the present: my role will follow at 11 am. Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee and Mahasveta Devi will attend.				 																Fusion fiesta				 																																	Tune in to Time Travil, a concert by Black Coffee, in association with St Xaviers College, at the college auditorium from 6 pm.				 																Melody magic				 																																	Spend a melodious evening with Ritwika Sahani at a concert at Kala Mandir at 6 pm.				 																Art on view				 																																	Visit Art of Bengal, a vision defined (1955-1975), an exhibition at CIMA Gallery from 2 pm to 7 pm. Sunday closed.
